Debuggability
The Devtools team is working on “basic support” for @function:
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/17UCa0XDXAG9EBx18w1fXAA9SL3V9Lr4vTptaXYyE1CA/"&gt;https://docs.google.com/document/d/17UCa0XDXAG9EBx18w1fXAA9SL3V9Lr4vTptaXYyE1CA/&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/17UCa0XDXAG9EBx18w1fXAA9SL3V9Lr4vTptaXYyE1CA/"&gt;https://docs.google.com/document/d/17UCa0XDXAG9EBx18w1fXAA9SL3V9Lr4vTptaXYyE1CA/&lt;/a&gt;&gt;
Unfortunately that doc requires @google.com &lt;&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://google.com"&gt;http://google.com&lt;/a&gt;&gt; to access, but “basic support” primarily means that callsites can be clicked, you’ll be taken to the relevant function, and you’ll be able to edit the contents of the function.
Will this feature be supported on all six Blink platforms (Windows, Mac, Linux, ChromeOS, Android, and Android WebView)?
Yes
