&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/blink/renderer/core/html/fenced_frame/html_fenced_frame_element.cc?q=%22HTMLFencedFrameElement.canLoadOpaqueURL"&gt;https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/blink/renderer/core/html/fenced_frame/html_fenced_frame_element.cc?q=%22HTMLFencedFrameElement.canLoadOpaqueURL&lt;/a&gt;()%20is%20deprecated%22&amp;ss=chromium%2Fchromium%2Fsrc&gt; 
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ever since pointing developers to the new API.
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;pre style="margin: 0em;"&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;tt&gt;The behavior of canLoadOpaqueURL() is not spec’d so this does not 
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;involve spec changes (only the explainer needs an update). The 
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;chromestatus metrics 
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://chromestatus.com/metrics/feature/timeline/popularity/5072"&gt;https://chromestatus.com/metrics/feature/timeline/popularity/5072&lt;/a&gt;&gt; 
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;shows there has been no usage of it for the last 6 months.
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;pre style="margin: 0em;"&gt;
How did we end up shipping an API that is not specified?
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;blockquote style="border-left: #5555EE solid 0.2em; margin: 0em; padding-left: 0.85em"&gt;&lt;pre style="margin: 0em;"&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;tt&gt;The removal of canLoadOpaqueURL() will start from M138. We would be 
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;happy to send out a formal Intent to Remove if anyone deems it worthwhile.
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;pre style="margin: 0em;"&gt;
